  "prompt": "What were the major events of Spain in 1492?",
  "response": "In 1492, Spain experienced several significant events:\n\n1. Completion of the Reconquista\n- On January 2, 1492, Granada, the last Muslim-controlled territory in the Iberian Peninsula, surrendered to the Catholic Monarchs Ferdinand II of Aragon and Isabella I of Castile, marking the end of the centuries-long Reconquista.\n\n2. Expulsion of Jews\n- On March 31, 1492, Ferdinand and Isabella issued the Alhambra Decree, ordering all Jews to either convert to Christianity or leave Spain within four months.\n\n3. Christopher Columbus's First Voyage\n- On August 3, 1492, Christopher Columbus set sail from Spain with three ships (the Ni\u00f1a, Pinta, and Santa Mar\u00eda) on his first voyage to find a western route to Asia.\n- On October 12, 1492, Columbus landed in the Bahamas, marking the beginning of European exploration and colonization of the Americas.\n\nThese events were crucial in Spanish history, transforming the country's religious, political, and global standing by completing the unification of Spain, expelling religious minorities, and initiating the Spanish colonial empire through Columbus's voyages.",
